Class Pair<F extends @Nullable Object,S extends @Nullable Object>

java.lang.Object
sprouts.Pair<F,S>
Type Parameters:
F - The type of the first value.
S - The type of the second value.
public final class Pair<F extends @Nullable Object,S extends @Nullable Object> extends Object
An immutable value object representing a pair of two generic values. Two pairs are considered equal if their first and second values are equal.
Use the of(Object, Object) factory method to create a new pair with the given values, and then use the first() and second() methods to access the values.
